            <scopecontent id="aspace_17e4308a7ca457fb8a0f2ac3b662bd82">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>William Rodman assembled his correspondence in six scrapbooks and created indexes for finding family names on the numbered pages within. After his death, work on the Pomeroy family genealogy was continued by his sister-in-law Rebekah Wheeler Pomeroy Bulkley (Mrs. Henry Thorp Bulkley, 1835-1908), and letters to her are in box 8.</p>
            </scopecontent>
